    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 6: CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS, RINGS AND
        SLEEVES - CYLINDER SLEEVE FITTING PROCEDURE - METHOD ONE, USE GRADUATED MARKS ON TOOL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>METHOD ONE, USE GRADUATED MARKS ON TOOL</title>
        <para>Use the following steps:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen locking screw.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the adjusting nut in a counterclockwise direction until the nut contacts the driver
                unit housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Back off the adjusting nut by the amount of cut desired.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Each graduated marking equals 0.025 mm (0.001 in.). If 0.050 mm (0.002 in.) material is to be
                        removed, you must back off the adjusting nut two (2) marks.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the adjusting nut lock screw.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>NEVER ATTEMPT TO REMOVE MORE THAN 0.050 mm (0.002 in.) MATERIAL AT ANY ONE TIME.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef1600634" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5254" filename="../figeg5/EG5254.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.34 Positioning The Counterbore Cutting Tool</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
